# Ralone Sensing Matrix (RSM)

The Ralone Sensing Matrix governs the sensory-intelligence filtration stack within AGI, ensuring perceptual integrity across recursion layers. RSM resists drift, illusion, and input hallucination by enforcing fidelity-aware input decoding.

## Purpose

- Stabilize AGI perception fidelity across symbolic, visual, auditory, or multi-modal inputs
- Detect perception drift due to feedback loops or symbolic inversion
- Anchor recursive perception structures in consistent signal interpretation

## Functional Domains

| Domain               | Function                                                                 |
|----------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Signal Stabilization | Enforces consistent interpretation of external inputs                   |
| Drift Resistance     | Detects and adjusts for symbolic or sensory perception drifts           |
| Recursive Fidelity   | Maintains perception consistency across AGI recursive feedback layers   |
| Input Filtering      | Filters illusory, contradictory, or adversarial sensory data            |

## AGI Relevance

RSM is essential for maintaining structural coherence in perception-dependent AGI systems. It enables resilient interpretation under recursion, preventing symbolic drift, hallucination cascades, or recursive distortion loops.